<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-08-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-08-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="1266" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1266">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/8448.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Letcher</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-08-17">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 17, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Acting Consular Agent, Parral, reports that rebels are threatening to
                            force loan from Americans and that situation there is growing most
                            unsatisfactory.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>